<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Irene B. Rosenfeld</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chairman of the Board and</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chief Executive Officer</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Three Parkway North</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Dear Fellow Shareholders: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We launched Mondel&#275;z International three-and-a-half years ago as a focused global snacking company. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Since that time, I&#146;m proud that we&#146;ve delivered industry-leading total shareholder returns that are well above the S&amp;P 500 and our consumer staples peers,
despite the highly volatile macroeconomic environment. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our hard-working colleagues have delivered these results by focusing on what we can control and transforming
our business to address the challenges head on. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We&#146;re building the world&#146;s best snacking company &#150; one capable of winning long-term by delivering
sustainable growth on both the top <U>and</U> bottom lines. That&#146;s what sets us apart from our competitors! </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As we prepare for our Annual Meeting of
Shareholders, allow me to share a few thoughts on where we&#146;ve been and where we&#146;re going, while highlighting a few of our recent successes. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><div style="width:100%;margin-left:0%; margin-right:0%;border:solid 2.00pt;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-top:6pt; margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>You&#146;re Invited! </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">I&#146;m pleased to invite you to our 2016 Annual Meeting of Shareholders. We will hold the meeting at 9 a.m. CDT on Wednesday, May 18,
2016, at NOAH&#146;s Event Venue in Lincolnshire, Ill. The center will open to shareholders at 8&nbsp;a.m. If you wish to attend the meeting, please register in advance by following the instructions included in the Proxy Statement. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-bottom:6pt; margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All shareholders of record as of March 9, 2016, are entitled to vote. As in the past, we&#146;re distributing proxy
materials with instructions on how to access these materials and on how to vote. Even if you plan to attend the meeting in person, we encourage you to vote in advance in one of three ways: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5"> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Leveraging Our Competitive Advantages</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:10pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ROWSPAN="13"> <P STYLE="font-size:62pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Sales by Category</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><I>Percentage of 2015</I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><I>Pro Forma Adjusted Net

<TD VALIGN="top"><B>A portfolio focused on large, fast-growing snacks</B>. Snacking is a $1.2 trillion market, and it&#146;s growing around the world. Snacks typically carry higher margins than other food categories, and consumption is
expandable.</TD>

chocolate, <I>Trident</I> in gum and <I>Halls</I> in candy. These are our largest, fastest-growing and highest-margin brands that account for nearly 70 percent<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">1</SUP> of our revenue.&nbsp;We also have a
number of proven global innovation platforms like <I>belVita</I>, <I>Barni</I> and <I>Oreo Thins</I> in biscuits as well as <I>Bubbly</I> and <I>Marvellous Creations</I> in chocolate.</FONT></TD>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Focusing on What We Can Control </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">While we remain optimistic in the long-term outlook, it&#146;s no secret that the global economy has become more challenging and volatile since we launched the company
in 2012. Growth in snacks categories and consumer demand in key emerging markets have slowed. At the same time, we&#146;ve experienced significant increases in input costs and strong currency headwinds. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To address these issues, we took significant steps over the past couple of years to adjust to the environment and take control of what we can by transforming the
business in the following ways: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="57%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="36%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="13"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="13" COLSPAN="2"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em">


<IMG SRC="g119433g13s86.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="3"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Focus our portfolio </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We continue to focus our
portfolio more firmly within our snacks categories.&nbsp;Last year, we combined our coffee business with D.E Master Blenders to create the Jacobs Douwe Egberts coffee venture &#150; the largest focused coffee company in the world. We also
strengthened our snacks business with two bolt-on acquisitions &#150; Kinh Do biscuits in Vietnam and Enjoy Life Foods in the U.S. As a result, snacks now represent about 85 percent<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">1</SUP> of our
revenue, up from 75 percent in 2014. We also improved our revenue mix by eliminating underperforming products and optimizing our promotional spending.</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="54"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="54" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="54" COLSPAN="2"></TD>

<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em">


<IMG SRC="g119433g13s86.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Reduce costs</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We continue to improve our margins. We
delivered record net productivity of more than 3.5 percent of cost of goods sold in 2015. We&#146;ve begun to see the benefits of our supply chain reinvention, as we upgrade our manufacturing network and install more efficient and flexible lines of
the future. In addition, we drove down our overhead costs through zero-based budgeting tools, and we&#146;re simplifying and standardizing various scalable, transactional processes through global shared services.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g119433g88o64.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD></TR>

<IMG SRC="g119433g13s86.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="3"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Invest for growth</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We continue to make
high-return investments to accelerate growth on our base business and address important consumer trends. Last year, we disproportionately supported our Power Brands and stepped up investments in sales and route-to-market capabilities in key emerging
markets so that we&#146;ll be well-positioned to capitalize on their long-term growth potential as the macroeconomic environment improves. We further focused our innovation efforts on key consumer needs, such as health &amp; wellness and <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">e-commerce.</FONT> We intend to be the global leader in well-being snacks, representing half of our revenue by 2020. In addition, we&#146;re building an industry-leading e-commerce snacks business, targeting $1 billion in
revenue by 2020. We&#146;re also broadening our portfolio beyond mainstream offerings to meet the needs of consumers both at the upper and lower ends of the economic spectrum.</P></TD></TR>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Delivering Strong Margin Expansion and Solid Earnings Growth </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2015, we delivered another year of very strong results.&nbsp;Our aggressive cost-savings programs drove significant margin expansion, enabling us to increase our
marketing investments, which accelerated organic revenue growth and improved our share performance as the year progressed. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<IMG SRC="g119433g13s86.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">Net revenues were $29.6 billion, down 13.5 percent. Pro Forma Organic Net Revenue<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">1</SUP> increased 1.4 percent, driven by our pricing actions to recover higher commodity- and
currency-driven input costs. Emerging markets grew nearly 5 percent despite weakening macroeconomic conditions. Our Power Brands, which were up 3 percent, continued to drive our top-line growth.</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="13"></TD>

</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">Operating income was $8.9 billion, up 174.4 percent. Pro Forma Adjusted Operating Income<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">2</SUP> margin increased 150 basis points to 13.2 percent. We accomplished this by reducing our
overhead costs as a percentage of revenue while also increasing advertising and consumer support for our brands.</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">

<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Accelerating Action with Our 2020 Global Sustainability Goals </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We believe that the growth of our business is inextricably linked to the well-being of the people who make and enjoy our products and the communities in which we live
and work.&nbsp;Our Call For Well-being therefore focuses where we can make the greatest impact, in the areas of sustainability, mindful snacking, community partnerships and safety. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Last year, we continued to progress our well-being agenda. Working with leading organizations, we&#146;re accelerating actions to address climate change through our new
sustainability goals, which focus on reducing key end-to-end environmental impacts, from the field through distribution. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">By 2020 (versus our 2013 baseline), we
will have: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top"><B>Reduced total manufacturing waste by 20 percent</B></TD></TR>

reconciliation in Exhibit A and the section entitled &#147;Non-GAAP Financial Measures&#148; in our Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December 31, 2015. Pro forma results exclude Venezuela. See Form 8-K dated February 3, 2016.

<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="7"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Empowering Cocoa Life Farmers</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In addition, we recently published the first progress report on Cocoa Life, our $400 million investment to empower 200,000 cocoa farmers and reach over one million
community members by 2022.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The progress report highlighted the wide-ranging impact of our
efforts to date across our six cocoa-growing origins: Ghana, C&ocirc;te d&#146;Ivoire, Indonesia, Dominican Republic, India and Brazil. Since the inception of Cocoa Life in 2012 through 2015, we have:</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-2.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>


<IMG SRC="g119433g13s86.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Reached 76,700 farmers in over 795 communities,</B> establishing a strong foundation and framework for the program</P></TD>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As the world&#146;s largest buyer of cocoa, we&#146;re committed to a sustainable cocoa supply chain. Ultimately, our goal is to
sustainably source all of our cocoa, and we&#146;re on track to get there. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Building on Our Momentum </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In closing, I&#146;m proud of our progress made since the launch of our company and especially pleased with our strong 2015 results. Our success is a tribute to our
world-class people, who have the passion, leadership, capabilities and experience to grow our business around the world. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">While we expect global economic
conditions, especially in emerging markets, to remain difficult in 2016, we&#146;ll build on our 2015 momentum by focusing on what we can control to again accelerate revenue growth and expand margins. By executing our strategies, we&#146;re
well-positioned to continue delivering strong returns to our shareholders now and over the long-term. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On behalf of all of our Mondel&#275;z International employees,
I thank you for your continued support of our company. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Best regards, </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Forward-Looking Statements </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">This letter to shareholders contains a number of forward-looking statements. Words, and variations of words, such as &#147;will,&#148; &#147;expect,&#148;
&#147;intend,&#148; &#147;believe,&#148; &#147;positioned,&#148; &#147;target,&#148; &#147;outlook&#148; and similar expressions are intended to identify our forward-looking statements, including, but not limited to, statements about: our future
performance, including our future revenue growth, earnings per share, margins and cash flow; growth in emerging markets; macroeconomic conditions; our supply chain transformation; overheads; shareholder returns; our well-being portfolio and goals;
revenues from e-commerce; and our 2020 global sustainability goals. These forward-looking statements are subject to a number of risks and uncertainties, many of which are beyond our control, which could cause our actual results to differ materially
from those indicated in our forward-looking statements. Such factors include, but are not limited to, risks from operating globally including in emerging markets; changes in currency exchange rates, controls and restrictions; continued volatility of
commodity and other input costs; weakness in economic conditions; weakness in consumer spending; pricing actions; unanticipated disruptions to our business; competition; our global workforce; the restructuring program and our other transformation
initiatives not yielding the anticipated benefits; changes in the assumptions on which the restructuring program is based; and tax law changes. Please also see our risk factors, as they may be amended from time to time, set forth in our filings with
the SEC, including our most recently filed Annual Report on Form 10-K. Mondel&#275;z International disclaims and does not undertake any obligation to update or revise any forward-looking statement in this letter to shareholders, except as required
by applicable law or regulation. </P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc119433_1"></A>Proxy Statement Summary </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>In this Proxy Statement Summary and throughout the Proxy Statement, &#147;we,&#148; &#147;us,&#148; &#147;our,&#148; &#147;the Company,&#148; and &#147;Mondel&#275;z
International,&#148; refer to Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>This summary highlights select information contained elsewhere in this Proxy Statement. You
should read the entire Proxy Statement carefully before voting and consider all information in the Proxy Statement. For more complete information regarding the Company&#146;s 2015 performance, please see our Annual Report on Form <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 (the &#147;2015 Form 10-K&#148;). </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>2016 Annual Meeting of
Shareholders (the &#147;Annual Meeting&#148;) </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">At the Annual Meeting, the persons named as proxies on each shareholder&#146;s proxy card will vote the shares represented by the proxy card FOR or AGAINST or ABSTAIN
from voting on each proposal, as indicated in the shareholder&#146;s voting instructions. If no indication is made on the properly executed proxy card, proxies will vote FOR each of the director nominees listed in proposal 1, FOR proposals 2 and 3,
AGAINST proposals 4, 5 and 6 and in their discretion upon such other business as properly comes before the meeting. </P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Voting at the Annual Meeting (Page 87 of this Proxy Statement) </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All shareholders of record as of March&nbsp;9, 2016 may vote in person at the meeting. Generally, beneficial owners may vote in person at the meeting if they have a
legal proxy, as described in the response to Question 14 on page 87 of this Proxy Statement. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Attending the Annual Meeting &#150; Important Note
About Advance Registration Process and Admission Requirements (Page 89 of this Proxy Statement) </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">If you plan to attend the meeting in person, see the answer to
Question 23 on page 89 of this Proxy Statement for important details on advance registration and admission requirements. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Frequently Asked

held in brokerage accounts and employee benefit plans, in the FAQ section beginning on page 84 of this Proxy Statement. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Items of Business

<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Corporate Governance Highlights (Pages 17 and 37 of this Proxy Statement) </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We believe that a strong and balanced corporate governance framework is essential to our long-term success because it promotes the long-term interests of shareholders,
accountability and trust in the Company. We highlight here key aspects of our corporate governance framework. Shareholders can find additional detail under &#147;Corporate Governance&#148; beginning on page 17 of this Proxy Statement and under
&#147;Our Executive Compensation Design Principles and Governance Practices&#148; on page 37 of this Proxy Statement. </P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>ITEM&nbsp;2. Advisory Vote to Approve Executive Compensation (Page 72 of this Proxy Statement)
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Compensation Goals </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Human Resources and Compensation Committee
has four primary goals for our executive compensation program: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">1.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Attract, retain and motivate talented executive officers and develop world-class business leaders; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">2.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Support business strategies that promote superior long-term shareholder returns; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">3.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Align pay and performance by making a significant portion of our Named Executive Officers&#146; (&#147;NEOs&#148;) compensation dependent on achieving financial and other critical strategic and individual goals; and
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">4.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Align our NEOs&#146; and shareholders&#146; interests through stock ownership and holding requirements and equity-based incentive grants that link executive compensation to sustained and superior Total Shareholder
Return<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> (&#147;TSR&#148;). </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Compensation Design </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We design our executive compensation program to achieve these goals by: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Linking pay to performance; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Putting pay at risk based on short-term and long-term performance; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

Compensation Discussion and Analysis beginning on page 34 of this Proxy Statement. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>ITEM&nbsp;3. Ratification of the Selection of
PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP as Independent Registered Public </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Accountants for Fiscal Year 2016 (Page 73 of this Proxy Statement) </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As a matter of good governance, we are asking our shareholders to ratify the Audit Committee&#146;s selection of PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP as our independent

<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Other Matters </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Other than Items 1 through 6 described in this
Proxy Statement, we do not expect any matters to be presented for action at the Annual Meeting. The Chairman of the Annual Meeting may refuse to allow presentation of an improperly submitted proposal or a nomination for the Board at the Annual
Meeting. We described the requirements for shareholders to properly submit proposals and nominations at the Annual Meeting in our 2015 Proxy Statement. Those requirements are similar to those described under &#147;2017 Annual Meeting of

such matters in accordance with their best judgment. </P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc119433_2"></A>ITEM&nbsp;1. Election of Directors </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_3"></A>Process for Nominating Directors </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance, Membership and Public Affairs Committee of our Board (the &#147;Governance Committee&#148;) is responsible for identifying, evaluating and recommending
to the Board director nominees for election at the Annual Meeting (and any adjournments or postponements of the meeting). The Governance Committee invites director nominee suggestions from the directors, shareholders, management and others. In
addition, the Governance Committee from time to time retains third-party executive search firms to assist in identifying and evaluating potential director nominees based on the Board&#146;s recruitment objectives. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>General Qualifications </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes all directors should possess
certain personal characteristics, including integrity, sound business judgment and vision. The Board believes these characteristics are necessary to establish a competent, ethical and well-functioning Board that best represents the interests of our
shareholders. Under our Corporate Governance Guidelines (the &#147;Guidelines&#148;), when evaluating the suitability of individuals for nomination, the Governance Committee takes into account many factors. These include the individual&#146;s
general understanding of the varied disciplines relevant to the success of a large, publicly traded company in today&#146;s global business environment, understanding of our global businesses and markets, professional expertise and educational
background, and other factors that promote diversity of views, knowledge and experience, including, among others, gender, race and national origin. The Governance Committee also considers an individual&#146;s ability to devote sufficient time and
effort to fulfill his or her responsibilities to the Company, given the individual&#146;s other commitments. In addition, the Governance Committee considers whether an individual meets various independence requirements, including whether his or her
service on boards and committees of other organizations is consistent with our conflicts of interest policy. The Governance Committee also evaluates each individual in the context of the Board as a whole, with the objective of recruiting and
recommending a slate of director nominees who can best perpetuate the Company&#146;s success and represent our shareholders&#146; interests through the exercise of sound judgment and informed decision-making. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In addition, under our Guidelines, the Governance Committee generally will not recommend, and the Board will not nominate an individual or re-nominate for election an
independent director after he or she reaches age 75. However, the Governance Committee and Board may do so in extraordinary circumstances if nomination or re-nomination is in the shareholders&#146; best interests because the candidate is uniquely
qualified to contribute to a specific dimension of the Board&#146;s work and the Company&#146;s growth in the subsequent year. If the Governance Committee determines that the individual&#146;s nomination or re-nomination for election is in the
shareholders&#146; best interests, the Governance Committee may recommend, and the Board may approve, that director&#146;s nomination or re-nomination for up to three annual terms following the director&#146;s 75th birthday. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">A management director must resign from the Board upon ceasing to be a Company officer. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Individual Experience, Qualifications, Attributes and Skills </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance
Committee works with the Board to determine the appropriate mix of characteristics, professional experience and areas of expertise that will result in a Board that is strong in its collective knowledge, allowing the Board to fulfill its
responsibilities and best perpetuate our long-term success and represent all shareholders&#146; interests. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under the leadership of the Lead Director and Chairman
of the Governance Committee, the Governance Committee annually conducts evaluations of the Board and the Board&#146;s committees. It also coordinates the directors&#146; self-assessments which the Governance Committee uses to assess the experience,
qualifications, attributes, skills, diversity and contributions of each director and of the Board as a whole. Every year, the director nominees complete questionnaires to update and confirm their background, qualifications, skills and potential
conflicts of interest. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;7 </FONT></P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Based upon the Governance Committee&#146;s discussions with the Board, the Governance Committee has identified the
following key competencies and relevant professional experience and areas of expertise that are particularly desirable for our directors to possess in order to meet the Board&#146;s current and future needs and obligations: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<I>Best in Class &#150; Manufacturing
Operations</I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<I>Best in Class &#150; Retail Operating
</I></P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#e5e5e5" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><I>Leadership Experience</I> which gives directors the ability to motivate, manage, identify and develop leadership qualities in others</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Board Composition and Diversity </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As noted above, the Guidelines provide that the Governance Committee will consider factors including, among others, gender, race and national origin that promote
diversity of views, knowledge and experience when evaluating the suitability of individuals for nomination. While the Board does not have a formal written policy regarding what specific factors would create such diversity, the Governance Committee
recognizes and strives to promote the significant benefit diversity provides to the Board and Mondel&#275;z International, as varying viewpoints contribute to a more informed and effective decision-making process. The Governance Committee seeks
broad experience in relevant industries, professions and areas of expertise important to our operations. Among them are: industry knowledge; substantial global business and other international experience and backgrounds given our global,
multicultural business; significant operating experience; leadership and people development experience; accounting and financial expertise; product development and marketing experience; and public company board and corporate governance experience.
As part of its periodic assessment of the Board&#146;s composition, the Governance Committee assesses the effectiveness of the Board&#146;s diversity. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our director
nominees&#146; varied and relevant experiences, global and diverse perspectives, backgrounds and personal characteristics provide the Board with a diversity of viewpoints and enable it to represent effectively our shareholders: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>

<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">12 have operating and general management experience at major companies, including food and beverage, consumer products and services, and manufacturing companies; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">4 are women, including the Chairman and CEO. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Size of Board </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Board currently has 13 directors. The Governance Committee recommended and the Board nominated each of the 13 incumbent directors listed below under
&#147;&#150;&nbsp;Director Nominees for Election at the 2016 Annual Meeting&#148; for election at the 2016 Annual Meeting. Each director nominee consented to his or her nomination for election to the Board and to serving on the Board, if elected.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Annual Elections </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Shareholders elect all directors annually. Of the 13
directors standing for election, shareholders elected 12 to one-year terms at the 2015 Annual Meeting of Shareholders. Christiana Shi was recommended to the Governance Committee as a potential director by the Governance Committee&#146;s consultant,
Heidrick&nbsp;&amp; Struggles, in connection with the Governance Committee&#146;s search for a director with significant e-commerce and global business experience. On December&nbsp;8, 2015, the Board appointed Ms.&nbsp;Shi, effective January&nbsp;4,
2016. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The terms of all directors elected at the 2016 Annual Meeting will end at the 2017 Annual Meeting of Shareholders or when a director&#146;s successor has
been duly elected and qualified. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Shareholder Recommendations of Candidates for Election to the Board </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance Committee welcomes shareholder recommendations of candidates for election to the Board. To recommend a particular candidate for consideration, the
shareholder should submit the required information to our Corporate Secretary, which information includes the name of the recommended candidate along with the same information required for a shareholder to nominate a candidate for election to the
Board at an Annual Meeting and in the same manner as set forth in the advance notice provisions of the Company&#146;s By-Laws. When evaluating a candidate recommended by a shareholder(s), the Governance Committee uses the same criteria set forth in
the Guidelines, as described above in this section, as it uses to evaluate a candidate the Governance Committee </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;9 </FONT></P>

identifies. It then makes a recommendation to the Board regarding the candidate&#146;s appointment or nomination for election to the Board at an upcoming annual meeting. After the Board&#146;s
consideration of the Committee&#146;s recommendation, our Corporate Secretary notifies that shareholder of the Board&#146;s decision whether to appoint or nominate the candidate. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In addition, our By-Laws permit our shareholders to nominate a candidate for election directly at an Annual Meeting or for inclusion in our proxy materials, subject to
certain terms and conditions. For details, see &#147;2017 Annual Meeting of Shareholders &#150; Shareholder Nominations and Proposals for the 2017 Annual Meeting&#148; on page 90 of this Proxy Statement. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_4"></A>Director Nominees for Election at the Annual Meeting </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Individual Nominees&#146; Experience, Qualifications, Attributes and Skills </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes that each director nominee for election at the Annual Meeting is highly qualified. The director nominees&#146; biographies describe the specific
experience, qualifications, including education and background, attributes and skills that the Governance Committee relied upon when determining to recommend the individual director nominees for election and led the Board to nominate him or her for
election. A particular director nominee may possess skills, knowledge or experience in addition to those described below. As their biographies indicate, all the director nominees possess significant leadership and professional experience, knowledge,
including industry knowledge, and skills that qualify them for service on our Board. Each director nominee other than Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld satisfies independence requirements under the NASDAQ listing standards and the Board&#146;s categorical
standards of director independence. All 13 director nominees satisfy the criteria stated in our Guidelines and possess the personal characteristics essential for the proper and effective functioning of the Board, including public board and corporate
governance experience. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Their biographies also include information about current and past (covering the last five years) directorships at companies publicly listed
in the U.S. and registered investment companies. The director nominees may also serve on the boards of various private companies, companies listed outside of the U.S. and charitable, educational and cultural institutions, not all of which are
included in their biographies. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">If a director nominee should become unavailable to serve as a director, the persons named as proxies intend to vote the shares for a
replacement director nominee designated by the Board. In lieu of naming a substitute, the Board may reduce the number of directors on our Board. </P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>THE BOARD RECOMMENDS SHAREHOLDERS VOTE FOR THE ELECTION OF EACH OF THESE 13 DIRECTOR NOMINEES. </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following information regarding each director nominee is as of March&nbsp;9, 2016. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="3"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>STEPHEN F. BOLLENBACH</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Former Co-Chairman and CEO, Hilton Hotels Corporation</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director Since October 2012; Independent</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Committee: Audit</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr.&nbsp;Bollenbach, 73, served as Co-Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Hilton Hotels
Corporation, a global hospitality provider, from May 2004 until his retirement in October 2007, and as President and Chief Executive Officer from February 1996 to May 2004. Prior to that, he was Senior Executive Vice President and Chief Financial
Officer of The Walt Disney Company, an international family entertainment and media enterprise, from September 1995 to February 1996. Mr.&nbsp;Bollenbach spent the previous 30 years in various financial leadership positions, including Chief
Financial Officer, in the family entertainment, media, hospitality, real estate and financial services industries. Mr.&nbsp;Bollenbach is a director of KB Home, Macy&#146;s Inc. and Time Warner Inc. and was formerly a director of Moelis&nbsp;&amp;
Company.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Leadership, Product Development and Marketing, Operating and
Global Business experience &#150; former Co-Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President of a global hospitality corporation;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Accounting and Financial expertise &#150; many years of
experience in financial leadership positions, including ten years as Chief Financial Officer, in the family entertainment, media, hospitality, real estate and financial services industries; and</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Public Company Board and Corporate Governance
experience.</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="3"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>LEWIS W.K. BOOTH</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Former Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer, Ford Motor Company</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since October 2012; Independent</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Committees: Finance</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:5.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Human Resources and
Compensation</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr.&nbsp;Booth, 67, served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of the Ford
Motor Company, a global automobile manufacturer, from November 2008 until his retirement in April 2012. He was Executive Vice President of Ford of Europe, Volvo Car Corporation and Ford Export Operations and Global Growth Initiatives, and Executive
Vice President of Ford&#146;s Premier Automotive Group from October 2005 to October 2008. Prior to that, Mr.&nbsp;Booth held various executive leadership positions with Ford, including Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Ford of Europe,
President of Mazda Motor Corporation and President of Ford Asia Pacific and Africa Operations. He worked continuously for the Ford Motor Company, in positions of increasing responsibility, from 1978 to 2012. Mr.&nbsp;Booth was appointed Commander of
the Order of the British Empire in June 2012 for his services to the United Kingdom&#146;s automotive and manufacturing industries. Mr.&nbsp;Booth is a director of Gentherm Incorporated and Rolls-Royce Holdings plc.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Leadership, Product Development and Marketing, Operating and
Global Business experience &#150; many years of experience in executive leadership positions for major divisions of a global automobile manufacturer, during which he successfully implemented major business restructuring and return to
profitability;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Accounting and Financial expertise &#150;
former Chief Financial Officer of a global automobile manufacturer, where he participated in a restructuring of the balance sheet and a return to growth and profitability; and</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Public Company Board and Corporate Governance
experience.</P></TD></TR>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>LOIS D. JULIBER</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Former Vice Chairman and Chief Operating Officer, Colgate-Palmolive Company</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since November 2007; Independent</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>

and Compensation</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Ms.&nbsp;Juliber, 67, served
as Vice Chairman of the Colgate-Palmolive Company, a global consumer products company, from October 2004 until her retirement in April 2005. She served as Colgate-Palmolive&#146;s Chief Operating Officer from February 2000 to October 2004, Executive
Vice President &#150; North America and Europe from 1997 until February 2000, President of Colgate North America from 1994 to 1997 and Chief Technology Officer from 1991 until 1994. Prior to joining Colgate-Palmolive, Ms.&nbsp;Juliber spent 15 years
at Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s predecessor, General Foods Corporation, in a variety of key marketing and general management positions. Ms.&nbsp;Juliber is a director of E. I. du Pont de Nemours and Company. She was formerly a director of
Goldman Sachs Group, Inc.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Leadership and Operating experience &#150; former Vice Chairman
and Chief Operating Officer of a global consumer products company, where she led the company&#146;s turn-around in North America and expansion and growth in key emerging markets like India and China;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Industry Knowledge, Manufacturing and Information Technology,
Product Development, Research and Development and Marketing, and Global Business and Supply Chain experience &#150; 32 years working in the global consumer products industry; and</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Public Company Board and Corporate Governance experience.</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Former President and Chief Executive Officer, Newell Rubbermaid Inc.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000"> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr.&nbsp;Ketchum, 66,
served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Newell Rubbermaid Inc., a global marketer of consumer and commercial products, from October 2005 until his retirement in June 2011 and was a member of its board of directors from November 2004 to
May 2012. From 1971 to 2004, Mr.&nbsp;Ketchum served in a variety of roles of increasing responsibility at The Procter&nbsp;&amp; Gamble Company, a global marketer of consumer products, including President, Global Baby and Family Care, from 1999 to
2004, President &#150; North American Paper Sector from 1996 to 1999, and Vice President and General Manager &#150; Tissue/Towel from 1990 to 1996. Mr.&nbsp;Ketchum was formerly a director of Newell Rubbermaid Inc.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P>

Chief Executive Officer of a global consumer products company and former President of a division of another global consumer products company;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Industry Knowledge, Product Development and Marketing and
Global Business experience &#150; held key roles in operations, marketing and general management at global consumer products companies for four decades; and</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Public Company Board and Corporate Governance experience.</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Former Chairman of the Board, Aramark</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since November 2014; Independent</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>

Chairman of the Board of Aramark, a leading provider of professional services including food, hospitality, facility and uniform services, from April 1984 until February 2015. Mr.&nbsp;Neubauer joined Aramark in 1979 as Executive Vice President of
Finance and Development, Chief Financial Officer and a member of the Board of Directors. He was elected President in 1981, Chief Executive Officer in 1983 and Chairman in 1984. He held the title of Chairman and CEO until May 2012. Mr.&nbsp;Neubauer
is a director of Macy&#146;s Inc. He was formerly a director of Aramark and Verizon Communications, Inc.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

a global provider of food, facilities and uniform services company;</P>

served as Chief Executive Officer and Founding Partner of Trian Fund Management, L.P., an alternative investment management firm, since November 2005. He also served as Chairman and CEO of Triarc Companies, Inc. (now known as The Wendy&#146;s
Company), a holding company for various consumer and industrial businesses, from April 1993 to June 2007, and has served as its non-executive Chairman since June 2007. Prior to that, Mr.&nbsp;Peltz served as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of
Trian Group, Limited Partnership, which provided investment banking and management services to entities controlled by Mr.&nbsp;Peltz and Peter May, from January 1989 to April 1993 and as Chairman and CEO of Triangle Industries, Inc., a manufacturer
of packaging products, from 1983 to December 1988. The National Association of Corporate Directors (NACD) recognized Mr.&nbsp;Peltz in 2010, 2011 and 2012 as among the most influential people in the global corporate governance arena. Mr.&nbsp;Peltz
is a director of The Madison Square Garden Company, SYSCO Corporation and The Wendy&#146;s Company. He was formerly a director of H. J. Heinz Company, Legg Mason, Inc. and Ingersoll-Rand plc.</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Audit</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chair, Finance</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000"> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr.&nbsp;Siewert, 60, has
served as a Managing Director for The Carlyle Group, L.P., a global alternative asset management firm, since April 2007. In that role, Mr.&nbsp;Siewert serves as a director of several public companies trading on the Hong Kong and Singapore stock
exchanges. Formerly, he was a senior executive with The Coca-Cola Company, a global beverage company, from August 2001 to March 2007 in various positions including Group President and Chief Operating Officer, Asia and a member of the Global
Executive Committee. Prior to that, he was with Eastman Kodak Company, a technology company focused on imaging products and services, from 1974 to 2001, serving in a variety of executive and managerial and director roles, including Chief Operating
Officer, Consumer Imaging and Senior Vice President and President of the Kodak Professional Division. Mr.&nbsp;Siewert is a director of Avery Dennison Corporation.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

1991. Dr.&nbsp;Simmons was a Fulbright Scholar to France from 1967 to 1968 and is a Chevalier of the French Legion of Honor. Dr.&nbsp;Simmons is a director of Fiat Chrysler Automobiles NV, Square, Inc. and Texas Instruments Incorporated (from which
she will retire in April 2016) and was formerly a director of Chrysler Group LLC.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="3" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>JEAN-FRAN&Ccedil;OIS M. L. VAN BOXMEER</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chairman of the Executive Board and Chief Executive Officer, Heineken N.V.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since January 2010; Independent</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Finance</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Human Resources and Compensation</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr.&nbsp;van Boxmeer, 54, has
been Chairman of the Executive Board and Chief Executive Officer of Heineken N.V., a global brewing company, since 2005 and a member of its Executive Board since 2001. He has been employed continuously by Heineken, in various capacities, in
positions of increasing responsibility, since 1984. Mr.&nbsp;van Boxmeer is a Member of the Shareholders Committee of Henkel AG&nbsp;&amp; Co. KGaA.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Leadership and Operating experience &#150; current Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of a global brewing company, where he led the company&#146;s significant global expansion, most
notably in Asian markets;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Industry Knowledge, Product
Development and Marketing and Global Business experience &#150; three decades in various positions, including key roles, at a global brewing company; and</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Public Company Board and Corporate Governance experience.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc119433_5"></A>Corporate Governance </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We
believe that a strong corporate governance framework is essential to our long-term success. This section describes our governance policies, key governance practices and Board leadership structure and oversight functions. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_6"></A>Governance Guidelines </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board
adopted Guidelines articulating our governance philosophy, practices and policies in a range of areas, including: the Board&#146;s role and responsibilities; Board composition and structure; responsibilities of the committees of the Board; CEO and
Board performance evaluations; and succession planning. At least annually, the Governance Committee reviews the Guidelines and recommends any changes to the Board. The Guidelines are available on our website at
<I><U>www.mondelezinternational.com/investors/corporate-governance</U></I>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_7"></A>Key Corporate Governance Practices </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">At least annually, we review our corporate governance practices to support the Board&#146;s independent leadership, accountability and oversight. Key aspects of our
corporate governance framework include: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Annual Election of Directors</I>. Our By-Laws provide that our shareholders elect all directors annually. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Proxy Access By-Law Provisions. </I>Following consultation with numerous shareholders, the Board amended our By-Laws effective October&nbsp;9, 2015 to provide for proxy access under the following key parameters:
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I></I>Minimum Ownership Threshold: 3%; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Ownership Duration: 3 years; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Maximum Nominations Permitted: <I>greater of</I> 20% or 2 directors; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Aggregation: no more than 20 shareholders may aggregate holdings to meet the minimum ownership threshold. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Majority and Confidential Voting in Uncontested Director Elections with a Director Resignation Policy</I>. Our By-Laws provide that, in an election in which the number of nominees for election equals the number of
directors to be elected, director nominees must be elected by a majority of the votes cast. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Special Meetings of Shareholders</I>. Our By-Laws allow shareholders of record of at least twenty percent (20%)&nbsp;of the voting power of the outstanding stock to call a special meeting of shareholders.
</TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;17 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Limitation on Management Directors</I>. Our Guidelines provide that the Board believes the Chairman and CEO generally should be the only member of management to serve as a director. Currently, our Chairman and CEO is
the only member of management serving on the Board. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Independent Committees</I>. All Board committees consist entirely of, and are chaired by, independent directors. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Executive Sessions</I>. At each in-person Board meeting, our independent directors meet without the CEO or any other members of management present to discuss substantive issues important to Mondel&#275;z
International, including matters concerning management. The Lead Director chairs these sessions. In some instances, a committee chair leads Board discussion of a topic relevant to that committee&#146;s remit. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Board, Committee and Director Self-Assessments.</I> The Governance Committee establishes and oversees processes for annual Board and committee assessments and coordinates individual director self-assessments. The
Board, committees and management use the results of these self-assessments in planning their work and subsequent governance decisions. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Shareholder Engagement</I>. As more fully described on page 23 of this Proxy Statement, we engage in ongoing dialogue with shareholders throughout the year. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Strategic Planning. </I>Every year, the Board devotes several days to review, discuss and challenge the Company&#146;s Strategic Plan. During the meeting, the Board meets with management to understand the Strategic
Plan&#146;s short-term and long-term objectives before deciding to endorse the Strategic Plan. At its meetings during the balance of the year, the Board and management track progress against the Strategic Plan&#146;s goals. The Company&#146;s goals
and executive compensation design are tied to a number of metrics critical to achieving the Strategic Plan and promoting long-term shareholder returns. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Annual Chairman and CEO Evaluation</I>. The Human Resources and Compensation Committee (the &#147;Compensation Committee&#148;) annually evaluates the Chairman and CEO&#146;s performance. The Compensation Committee
seeks input from the other directors regarding her performance before deciding her performance rating. The Governance Committee annually considers the CEO&#146;s performance and suitability as Chairman when determining whether to nominate her for
re-election. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Stock Ownership Guidelines</I>. To promote alignment of directors&#146; and shareholders&#146; interests, our Guidelines provide that we expect directors to hold Common Stock in an amount equal to five times the
annual Board retainer within five years of joining the Board. As of March&nbsp;9, 2016, all directors with at least five years of service on the Board met or exceeded this requirement. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:10%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Additionally, equity grants awarded in or after May 2010 to directors are made in the form of deferred stock units. Distribution of actual shares occurs
six months after the director ends his or her service as a director. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Leadership Structure. </I>Our Guidelines currently provide for an independent Lead Director and that the CEO also serves as Chairman of the Board. See additional discussion below under &#147;&#150; Board Leadership
Structure.&#148; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Special Meetings of the Board</I>. Our By-Laws empower both the Lead Director and the Chairman to call special meetings of the Board. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_8"></A>Board Leadership Structure </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our
By-Laws provide the Board flexibility in determining its leadership structure. The Board may appoint and designate the duties of a Lead Director and permit one person to hold the offices of both CEO and Chairman. Within that framework, the Board
annually re-evaluates its leadership structure to determine the most appropriate leadership structure at that time. In considering which leadership structure will allow it to most effectively carry out its responsibilities and best represent
shareholders&#146; interests, the Board takes into account various factors. Among them are our specific business needs, our operating and financial performance, industry conditions, economic and regulatory environments, results of Board and
committee annual self-assessments, advantages and disadvantages of alternative leadership structures based on circumstances at that time and our corporate governance practices. In keeping with this principle, the Board may determine that the CEO
also serve as Chairman, but if it does so, it also appoints an independent Lead Director with robust responsibilities. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;18 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Current Leadership Structure </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Currently, our Guidelines provide that: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">an independent director serves as Lead Director; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
