<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">independent directors chair the Board&#146;s four standing committees; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the CEO serves as Chairman of the Board. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes that this leadership structure provides an effective
balance of strong leadership and independent oversight and best meets our current circumstances and anticipated needs. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Independent Director Leadership and
Oversight </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes that robust independent Board leadership and oversight are very important. Therefore, it established the substantive position of
independent Lead Director for times when one individual serves as both Chairman and CEO. Our independent directors annually select our Lead Director for a one-year term. The Board created the Lead Director position to provide independent leadership
of the Board&#146;s affairs on behalf of our shareholders, increase the Board&#146;s effectiveness, promote open communication amongst the independent directors and serve as the principal liaison between the Chairman and the other independent
directors. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Lead Director Role and Responsibilities </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under our
Guidelines, the Lead Director, in consultation with the other independent directors, has the following duties and responsibilities: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Serve as liaison between the independent directors and the Chairman and CEO; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">With respect to long-term meeting planning, seek input from the independent directors and advise the Chairman and CEO as to an appropriate annual schedule of and major agenda topics for regular Board meetings prior to
Board review and approval; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

agenda as well as the content of Board briefing materials; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

current Lead Director. The independent directors first appointed him to that role in 2009 and have re-appointed him annually. The independent directors believe that he is an effective Lead Director due to his independence, leadership, global
operating experience as former President and CEO of Newell Rubbermaid Inc. and a variety of roles during his 33 year career at The Procter&nbsp;&amp; Gamble Company, and corporate governance experience, including his prior service as a director of
Newell Rubbermaid Inc. and Hillenbrand Industries. </P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Chairman and CEO Role and Responsibilities </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld has served as our CEO and as a director since June 2006. In conjunction with our 2007 spin-off from Altria Group, Inc., the Board concluded that
Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld should also serve as Chairman because of her extensive knowledge of the Company, the food industry and the competitive environment in which we operate, her leadership experience and her ability and dedication to working closely
with the Lead Director and our other independent directors. Based on our current circumstances and anticipated needs, the Board continues to believe that having Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld serve as both CEO and Chairman serves our shareholders&#146;
interests and contributes to the Board&#146;s efficiency and effectiveness. The Board believes that she is generally in the best position to inform our independent directors about our global operations and critical business matters and ensure
alignment of our business and strategic plans. Further, the Board believes that combining these roles also fosters expedient communication between Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld and the Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_9"></A>Director Independence </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our
Guidelines require that at least 80% of our directors meet the NASDAQ listing standards&#146; independence requirements and provide that the Chairman and CEO generally should be the only member of management to serve as a director. In order to
determine that a director is independent, the Board must affirmatively determine, after reviewing all relevant information, that a director has no relationship with Mondel&#275;z International or any of its subsidiaries that would interfere with the
exercise of independent judgment in carrying out the responsibilities of a director. To assist in this determination, the Board adopted categorical standards of director independence, including whether a director or a member of the director&#146;s
immediate family has any current or past employment or affiliation with Mondel&#275;z International or our independent registered public accountants. These standards are generally consistent with the NASDAQ listing standards&#146; independence
requirements. Annex A to the Guidelines lists these categorical standards. It is available on our website at <I><U><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">www.mondelezinternational.com/investors/corporate-governance</FONT></U></I>. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board determined that, under our categorical standards and NASDAQ&#146;s listing standards, the following directors are independent: Stephen F. Bollenbach, Lewis
W.K. Booth, Lois D. Juliber, Mark D. Ketchum, Jorge S. Mesquita, Joseph Neubauer, Nelson Peltz, Fredric G. Reynolds, Christiana S. Shi, Patrick T. Siewert, Ruth J. Simmons and Jean-Fran&ccedil;ois M. L. van Boxmeer. In addition, Ratan N. Tata was
independent during the portion of fiscal 2015 he served on the Board. Irene B. Rosenfeld is not independent because she is a Mondel&#275;z International employee. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_10"></A>Oversight of Risk Management </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our
business faces various risks, including strategic, financial, operational and compliance risks. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Management is responsible for the day-to-day assessment, management and mitigation of risk. Identifying, managing and mitigating our exposure to these risks and effectively overseeing this process are critical to our
operational decision-making and annual planning processes. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our Board has ultimate responsibility for risk oversight, but it has delegated primary responsibility for overseeing risk assessment and management to the Audit Committee. Pursuant to its charter, the Audit Committee
reviews and discusses risk assessment and risk management guidelines, policies and processes utilized in our Enterprise Risk Management (&#147;ERM&#148;) process. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our ERM process is ongoing and implemented at all levels of our operations and across business units to identify, assess, monitor, manage and mitigate risk. Our ERM
process facilitates open communication between management and the Board so that the Board and committees understand key risks to our business and performance, our risk management process and how it is functioning, the participants in the process and
the information gathered through the process. The Audit Committee annually reviews the functioning of our ERM process as well as the results of our annual ERM risk assessment. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Annually, the Audit Committee reviews and approves management&#146;s recommendation for allocating to the full Board or retaining for itself responsibility for
reviewing and assessing key risk exposures and management&#146;s response to </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;20 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
those exposures. Management provides reports to the Board and the appropriate committee in advance of meetings regarding key risks and the actions management has taken to monitor, control and
mitigate these risks. Management also attends Board and committee meetings to discuss these reports and provide any updates. The committees report key risk discussions to the Board following their meetings. Board members may also further discuss the
risk management process directly with members of management. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">During 2015, the Board and committees reviewed and assessed risks related to our business and
operations as follows (the Board annually reviews and sometimes reallocates responsibilities amongst committees. Accordingly, the allocation of responsibilities shown in this table may change during 2016): </P>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Strategy</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Operations</P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Food safety (including supply chain and food defense)</P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Competition (including private label and customer concentration)</P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Capital structure</P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Financial strategies and transactions (including economic trends)</P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Labor relations (including human capital)</P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Transformation (including zero-based budgeting, supply chain reinvention and the coffee transaction)</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5e5e5" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf" BGCOLOR="#e5e5e5"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Financial statements</P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Financial reporting process</P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Accounting matters</P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Legal, compliance and regulatory matters (including non-financial compliance risks)</P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Succession planning</P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">For a discussion about risk oversight relating to our compensation programs, see &#147;&#150; Board Committees and Membership &#150; Human Resources and Compensation Committee &#150; How the Compensation Committee
Manages Compensation-Related Risk.&#148; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board frequently discusses our strategic plans, issues and opportunities in light of circumstances in
the food and beverage industry and the economic environment. Additionally, the Board devotes several days each year to a highly-focused review of our strategic plans, including strategic and operational risks. More generally, the Board is
responsible for oversight of strategy, broad corporate policy and overall performance of the Company through engaged oversight of management. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes
our current leadership structure enhances its oversight of risk management because our CEO, who is ultimately responsible for our risk management process, is in the best position as Chairman to discuss with the Board these key risks and
management&#146;s responses to them. </P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_11"></A>Codes of Conduct </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for Non-Employee Directors </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We have
adopted a Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for Non-Employee Directors. It fosters a culture of honesty and integrity, focuses on areas of ethical risk, guides non-employee directors in recognizing and handling ethical issues and provides
mechanisms to report unethical conduct. Annually, each non-employee director must acknowledge in writing that he or she has received, reviewed and understands the Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for Non-Employee Directors. Shareholders and
others can access our Director Ethics Code on our website at <I><U>www.mondelezinternational.com/investors/corporate-governance</U>. </I> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Code of Conduct for
Employees </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We have adopted a Code of Conduct for Employees that applies to all of our employees. It includes policies that cover ethical and legal practices for
nearly every aspect of our business. The Code of Conduct for Employees reflects our values and contains important rules our employees must follow when conducting business. The Code of Conduct is part of our global compliance and integrity program.
The program provides training throughout our Company and encourages reporting of wrongdoing by offering anonymous reporting options and a non-retaliation policy. Shareholders and others can access our Code of Conduct for Employees on our website at
<I><U>www.mondelezinternational.com/about-us/compliance-and-integrity</U></I>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We will disclose in the Corporate Governance section of our website any amendments
to our Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for Non-Employee Directors or Code of Conduct for Employees and any waiver granted to an executive officer or director under these codes. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_12"></A>Review of Transactions with Related Persons </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Related Persons Policy and Procedures </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board has adopted a written policy
regarding the review, approval or ratification of &#147;related person transactions.&#148; A related person transaction is one in which Mondel&#275;z International is a participant, the amount involved exceeds $120,000 and any &#147;related
person&#148; had, has or will have a direct or indirect material interest. In general, &#147;related persons&#148; are the following persons and their immediate family members: our directors, executive officers and shareholders beneficially owning
more than 5% of our outstanding Common Stock. In accordance with this policy, the Governance Committee reviews transactions that might qualify as related person transactions. If the Governance Committee determines that a transaction qualifies as a
related person transaction, then the Governance Committee reviews, and approves, disapproves or ratifies the related person transaction. The Governance Committee approves or ratifies only those related person transactions that are fair and
reasonable to Mondel&#275;z International and in our and our shareholders&#146; best interests. The chair of the Governance Committee reviews and approves or ratifies potential related person transactions when it is not practicable or desirable to
delay review of a transaction until a committee meeting. The chair reports to the Governance Committee any transaction so approved or ratified. The Governance Committee, in the course of its review and approval or ratification of a related person
transaction under this policy, considers, among other things: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">its commercial reasonableness; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the materiality of the related person&#146;s direct or indirect interest in it; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">whether it may involve an actual, or create the appearance of a, conflict of interest; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">its impact on the related person&#146;s independence (as defined in our Guidelines and the NASDAQ listing standards); and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">whether it would violate any provision of our Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for Non-Employee Directors or Code of Conduct for Employees. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Any member of the Governance Committee who is a related person with respect to a transaction under review may not participate in the deliberations or decisions
regarding the transaction. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;22 </FONT></P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Review of Transactions </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On
February&nbsp;10, 2016, BlackRock, Inc. (&#147;BlackRock&#148;), an investment management corporation, filed a Schedule 13G/A with the SEC reporting that it was a greater than 5% shareholder as of December&nbsp;31, 2015. During 2015, BlackRock acted
as an investment manager with respect to certain investment options under our U.S. retirement savings plans and Canadian, Irish and U.K. pension plans. BlackRock was selected as an investment manager for the retirement savings and pension plans by
each plan&#146;s designated authority for plan investments. BlackRock&#146;s selection was based on the determination of each plan&#146;s designated authority that the selection met applicable standards and that the fees were reasonable and
appropriate. BlackRock&#146;s fees, approximately $1.59 million during 2015, were paid from the plan assets of the specific plans for which it performed services. The plans expect to pay similar fees to BlackRock during 2016 for similar services.
(Fees, based on plan asset value, are paid quarterly on a lagging basis.) </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_13"></A>Shareholder Engagement </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Consistent with our shareholder engagement philosophy, throughout 2015, our Lead Director, senior management, Investor Relations and the Corporate Secretary met with
and sought feedback from many shareholders representing a significant portion of our outstanding shares on a wide range of topics including, among others, portfolio strategy, capital allocation, corporate governance including proxy access,
sustainability and corporate social responsibilities. These meetings were candid and constructive. We will continue to engage with and consider our shareholders&#146; perspectives, and doing so benefits Mondel&#275;z International and its
registered, beneficial, retail and institutional investors. Our Lead Director is available for consultation and direct communication with major shareholders. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><I><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s</FONT></I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><I><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Shareholder Engagement Philosophy</FONT></I></FONT></P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5e5e5" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_14"></A>Communications with the Board </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Information for shareholders and other parties interested in communicating with the Lead Director, the Board or our independent directors, individually or as a group,
is available on our website at <I><U>www.mondelezinternational.com/Investors/corporate-governance#contacts</U>.</I> Our Corporate Secretary: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Forwards communications relating to matters within the Board&#146;s purview to the Lead Director or appropriate independent director(s) and communications relating to matters within a Board committee&#146;s area of
responsibility to the chair of the appropriate committee. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

any independent director who requests them. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Does not forward or retain solicitations, junk mail and obviously frivolous or inappropriate communications. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc119433_15">
</A>Board Committees and Membership </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance Committee considers and makes recommendations to the Board regarding the Board&#146;s committee structure and
membership. Our Board designates the committee members and chairs following consideration of the Governance Committee&#146;s recommendations. The Board has adopted a written charter for each standing committee. The charters define each
committee&#146;s roles and responsibilities. Charters for each committee are available on our website at <I><U>www.mondelezinternational.com/investors/corporate-governance</U></I>. Independent directors comprise 100% of the Audit, Compensation,
Finance and Governance Committees. All committee chairs are independent. Each committee meets regularly in executive session without management. Committee Chairs approve agendas and materials for their committee meetings. In addition, committees may
retain outside legal, financial and other advisors, at the Company&#146;s expense. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;23 </FONT></P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

Compensation. The committee structure and membership is as follows: </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_16"></A>Committee Membership<SUP

<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_17"></A>Meeting Attendance </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We expect
directors to attend all Board meetings, the Annual Meeting and all meetings of the committees on which they serve. We understand, however, that occasionally a director may be unable to attend a meeting. The Board held eight meetings during 2015 and
acted twice by unanimous written consent. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">All incumbent directors who served for some or all of 2015 attended at least 75% of the aggregate number of meetings of the Board and all committees on which they served (held during the period that they served).
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">During 2015, Mses. Juliber and Rosenfeld and Messrs. Bollenbach, Booth, Ketchum and Reynolds attended 100% and Ms.&nbsp;Simmons and Messrs. Mesquita, Neubauer, Peltz, Siewert and van Boxmeer attended at least 84% of
meetings of the Board and all committees on which they served. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">All 12 of the then-incumbent directors attended the 2015 Annual Meeting of Shareholders. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_18">
</A>Audit Committee </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board established the Audit Committee in accordance with Section&nbsp;3(a)(58)(A) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (the
&#147;Exchange Act&#148;). The Board has determined that all of the Audit Committee members are independent within the meaning of the NASDAQ listing standards and Rule 10A-3 of the Exchange Act. The Board also determined that all Audit Committee
members are able to read and understand financial statements in accordance with NASDAQ listing standards and are financially literate in accordance with the New York Stock Exchange listing standards. The Board has determined that Stephen F.
Bollenbach and Fredric G. Reynolds are <I>&#147;</I>audit committee financial experts&#148; within the meaning of SEC regulations and have financial sophistication in accordance with NASDAQ listing standards. No Audit Committee member received any
payments in 2015 from us other than compensation for service as a director. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;24 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under its charter, the Audit Committee is responsible for overseeing our accounting and financial reporting processes and
audits of our financial statements. The Audit Committee is directly responsible for the appointment, compensation, retention and oversight of our independent registered public accountants, including review of their qualifications, independence and
performance. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Among other duties, the Audit Committee also oversees: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the integrity of our financial statements, our accounting and financial reporting processes, and our systems of internal control over financial reporting and safeguarding our assets; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">our compliance with legal and regulatory requirements; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the performance of our internal auditors and internal audit functions; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">our guidelines and policies with respect to risk assessment and risk management. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Audit Committee has established
procedures for the receipt, retention and treatment, on a confidential basis, of any complaints we receive. We encourage employees and third-party individuals and organizations to report concerns about our accounting controls, auditing matters or
anything else that appears to involve financial or other wrongdoing. To report such matters, please e-mail us at: <U>compliance@mdlz.com</U>. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><div style="width:100%;margin-left:0%; margin-right:0%;background-color:#eaeaea;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-top:6pt; margin-left:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc119433_19"></A>Audit Committee Report for the Year Ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; margin-right:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Management has primary responsibility for Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s financial statements and the reporting process, including
the systems of internal control over financial reporting. Our role as the Audit Committee of the </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; margin-right:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mondel&#275;z International Board
of Directors is to oversee Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s accounting and financial reporting processes and audits of its financial statements. In addition, in 2015 we assisted the Board in its oversight of: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s compliance with legal and regulatory requirements; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The performance of Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s internal auditor and the internal audit function; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s risk assessment and risk management guidelines and policies. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; margin-right:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our duties include overseeing Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s management, the internal audit department and the independent
registered public accountants in their performance of the following functions, for which they are responsible: </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Management </I></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>

<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Preparing Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s consolidated financial statements in accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America (&#147;U.S. GAAP&#148;); </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Internal Audit Department </I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <div style="width:100%;margin-left:0%; margin-right:0%;background-color:#eaeaea;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-top:0pt; margin-left:2%; margin-right:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Periodically, we meet, both independently and collectively, with management, the internal auditor and the independent
registered public accountants to, among other things: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Discuss the quality of Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s accounting and financial reporting processes and the adequacy and effectiveness of its internal controls and procedures; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Review significant audit findings prepared by each of the independent registered public accountants and internal audit department, together with management&#146;s responses; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Review the overall scope and plans for the audits by the internal audit department and the independent registered public accountants. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; margin-right:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Prior to Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s filing of its Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 with the
SEC, we also: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reviewed and discussed the audited financial statements with management and the independent registered public accountants; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Discussed with the independent registered public accountants the items the independent registered public accountants are required to communicate to the Audit Committee in accordance with the applicable requirements of
the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Received from the independent registered public accountants the written disclosures and the letter required by applicable requirements of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board regarding the independent
registered public accountants&#146; communications with us concerning independence; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Discussed with the independent registered public accountants their independence from Mondel&#275;z International, including reviewing non-audit services and fees to assure compliance with (i)&nbsp;regulations
prohibiting the independent registered public accountants from performing specified services that could impair their independence, and (ii)&nbsp;Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s and the Audit Committee&#146;s policies. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; margin-right:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Based upon the review and discussions described in this report and without other independent verification, and subject to the
limitations of our role and responsibilities outlined in this report and in our written charter, we recommended to the Board, and the Board approved, that the audited consolidated financial statements be included in Mondel&#275;z
International&#146;s Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, which was filed with the U. S. Securities and Exchange Commission on February&nbsp;19, 2016. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Audit Committee: </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; margin-right:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Fredric G.
Reynolds, Chair </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; margin-right:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Stephen F. Bollenbach </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; margin-right:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Jorge S. Mesquita </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; margin-right:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Patrick T. Siewert </P></div> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc119433_20">
</A>Pre-Approval Policies </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Audit Committee&#146;s policy is to pre-approve all audit and non-audit services provided by the independent registered public
accountants. These services may include audit services, audit-related services, tax services and other permissible non-audit services. The pre-approval authority details the particular service or category of service that the independent registered
public accountants will perform. Management reports to the Audit Committee on the actual fees charged by the independent registered public accountants for each category of service. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">During the year, circumstances may arise when it becomes necessary to engage the independent registered public accountants for additional services not contemplated in
the original pre-approval authority. In those instances, the committee approves the services before we engage the independent registered public accountants. In case approval is needed before a scheduled committee meeting, the committee has delegated
pre-approval authority to its chair. The chair must report on such pre-approval decisions at the committee&#146;s next regular meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Audit Committee
pre-approved all 2015 audit and non-audit services provided by the independent registered public accountants. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Audit Fees include (a)&nbsp;the integrated audit of our consolidated financial statements, including statutory audits of the financial
statements of our affiliates, and our internal control over financial reporting and (b)&nbsp;the reviews of our unaudited condensed consolidated interim financial statements (quarterly financial statements). </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Audit-Related Fees include professional services in connection with employee benefit plan audits, due diligence related to acquisitions and divestitures and procedures
related to various other audit and special reports. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Tax Fees include professional services in connection with tax compliance and advice. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All Other Fees include professional services in connection with seminars, compliance reviews and data protection compliance reviews. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All fees above include out-of-pocket expenses. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_22">
</A>Finance Committee </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board has determined that all of the Finance Committee members are independent within the meaning of the NASDAQ listing standards.
The Finance Committee&#146;s charter sets out its responsibilities, which include reviewing and making recommendations to the Board on significant financial matters, including: </P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_23"></A>Governance, Membership and Public Affairs Committee </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board has determined that all of the Governance Committee members are independent within the meaning of the NASDAQ listing standards. The Governance
Committee&#146;s charter sets out its responsibilities. Among its responsibilities are: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">recommend frequency of Board meetings and content of Board agendas; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">advise and make recommendations to the Board on corporate governance matters, including regarding our Guidelines and the annual self-assessments process for the Board, its committees, and its directors;
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">administer the Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for Non-Employee Directors and monitor directors&#146; compliance with our stock ownership guidelines; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">oversee policies and programs related to corporate citizenship, social responsibility and public policy issues significant to Mondel&#275;z International such as sustainability and environmental responsibility; food
labeling, marketing and packaging; and philanthropic and political activities and contributions; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">monitor issues, trends, internal and external factors and relationships that may affect Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s public image and reputation. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc119433_24"></A>Human Resources and Compensation Committee </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc119433_25"></A>Human Resources and Compensation Committee Independence, Interlocks and Insider Participation </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board has determined that all of the Compensation Committee members are independent within the meaning of the NASDAQ listing standards, including the heightened
independence criteria for compensation committee members. None of the Compensation Committee&#146;s members is or was: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">an officer or employee of Mondel&#275;z International; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">a participant in a &#147;related person&#148; transaction during 2015 (for a description of our policy on related person transactions, see &#147;Corporate Governance &#150; Review of Transactions with Related
Persons&#148; above); or </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

our annual report and Proxy Statement. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee has the authority to delegate any of its responsibilities to the committee&#146;s
Chair, another Compensation Committee member or a subcommittee of Compensation Committee members, unless prohibited by law, regulation or any NASDAQ listing standard. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc119433_27"></A>The Compensation Committee&#146;s Use of an Independent Compensation Consultant </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee retains an independent compensation consultant to assist it in evaluating executive compensation programs and advise it regarding the amount
and form of executive and director compensation. It uses a consultant to provide additional assurance that our executive and director compensation programs are reasonable, competitive and consistent with our objectives. It directly engages the
consultant under an engagement letter that the Compensation Committee reviews at least annually. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Since September 2009, the Compensation Committee has retained
Compensation Advisory Partners, LLC (&#147;CAP&#148;) as its independent compensation consultant, and the Compensation Committee annually reviews CAP&#146;s engagement. During 2015, CAP provided the Compensation Committee advice and services,
including: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">regularly participating in Compensation Committee meetings including executive sessions that exclude management; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">providing competitive peer group compensation data for executive positions and evaluating how the compensation we pay our NEOs (as described under &#147;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#148;) relates both to the
Company&#146;s performance and to how our peers compensate their executives; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">advising on the composition of our Compensation Survey Group and our Performance Peer Group (as described in the &#147;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#148;) that we use for benchmarking pay and performance;
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">updating the Compensation Committee on executive compensation trends, issues and regulatory developments; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">assessing and recommending non-employee director compensation. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, CAP provided
no services to Mondel&#275;z International other than consulting services to the Compensation Committee regarding executive and non-employee director compensation. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee regularly reviews the current engagements and the objectivity and independence of the advice that CAP provides to the Compensation Committee
on executive and non-employee director compensation. The Compensation Committee considered the six specific independence factors adopted by the SEC and NASDAQ and determined that CAP is independent and that CAP&#146;s work did not raise any
conflicts of interest. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc119433_28"></A>Limited Role of Executive Officers in the Determination of Executive Compensation and Non-Employee Director
Compensation </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Each year, our CEO presents compensation recommendations for her direct reports and our other executive officers, including the NEOs. The Compensation Committee reviews and discusses these recommendations with the CEO,
but retains full discretion over these compensation actions. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;29 </FONT></P>

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our CEO does not make recommendations or participate in deliberations regarding her own compensation. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Executive officers do not play a role in determining or recommending the amount or form of non-employee director compensation. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc119433_29"></A>How the Compensation Committee Manages Compensation-Related Risk </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As it does each year, in 2015, the Compensation Committee evaluated whether our compensation designs, policies and practices operate to discourage our executive officers
and other employees from taking unnecessary or excessive risks. As described in the &#147;Compensation Discussion and Analysis,&#148; we design our compensation to incentivize executives and other employees to achieve the Company&#146;s financial
and strategic goals as well as individual performance goals that promote long-term shareholder returns. Our compensation design discourages our executives and other employees from taking excessive risks for short-term benefits that may harm the
Company and our shareholders in the long-term. The Compensation Committee uses various strategies to mitigate risk, including: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">using both short-term and long-term performance-based compensation so that executives do not focus solely on short-term performance; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">weighting executive compensation heavily toward long-term incentives to encourage sustainable shareholder value and accountability for long-term results; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">using multiple relevant performance measures in our incentive plan designs so that executives do not place undue importance on one measure which could distort the results that we want to incent; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">weighting business and individual performance in our annual cash incentive program so that executives and employees do not have too narrow a focus; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">capping the amount of incentives that may be awarded or granted; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">retaining discretion to reduce incentive awards based on unforeseen or unintended consequences and clawback compensation in specified circumstances; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">requiring our top executives to hold a significant amount of their compensation in Company stock and prohibit them from hedging, pledging or engaging in short sales of their stock; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">not using employment contracts; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">not backdating or re-pricing option grants; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">not paying severance benefits on change in control unless the affected executive is first involuntarily terminated without cause or terminates due to good reason. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In addition, our Audit Committee oversees our ethics and compliance programs that educate executives and other employees on appropriate behavior and the consequences of
inappropriate actions. These programs not only drive compliance and integrity but also encourage employees with knowledge of bad behavior to report concerns by providing multiple reporting avenues while protecting reporting employees against
retaliation. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">CAP also reviewed the Compensation Committee&#146;s risk analysis, including the underlying procedures, and confirmed the Compensation
Committee&#146;s conclusion below. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In light of these analyses, the Compensation Committee believes that our compensation programs do not create risks that are
reasonably likely to have a material adverse effect on the Company. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc119433_30"></A>Compensation of Non-Employee Directors </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Any director who also is an employee of Mondel&#275;z International receives no compensation for service as a director. Currently, Irene B. Rosenfeld is the only
director who is an employee of the Company. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We strive to recruit and retain highly qualified non-employee directors who will best represent our shareholders&#146;
interests. To ensure the compensation we offer is sufficient to meet our objective, our Compensation Committee periodically reviews non-employee director compensation. During 2015, the Compensation Committee used data
</P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;30 </FONT></P>

provided by CAP to benchmark our non-employee director compensation against our Compensation Survey Group and compensation paid to non-employee directors of other Fortune 100 companies in order
to assess the appropriateness of the form and amount of non-employee director compensation. Based upon that information, the Compensation Committee recommended and the Board approved changes to the non-employee compensation in 2015. Effective
July&nbsp;1, 2015: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The annual retainer for the chairs of the Audit Committee and the Human Resources and Compensation Committee increased from $20,000 to $25,000; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The annual retainer for the chair of the Governance, Membership and Public Affairs Committee increased from $15,000 to $20,000. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Additionally, effective on May&nbsp;20, 2015, the date of the 2015 Annual Meeting of Shareholders, the annual equity grant value increased from $145,000 to $160,000.

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Cash Compensation &#150; Board, Lead Director and Committee Chair Retainers </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We pay our non-employee directors their cash retainers quarterly. Pursuant to the Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. 2001 Compensation Plan for Non-Employee Directors,
they can defer 25%, 50%, 75% or 100% of their cash retainers into notional unfunded accounts that mirror certain of the investment options under the Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Thrift 401(k) Plan. If the Board appoints a non-employee director during
the year (i.e., other than at the annual meeting of shareholders), we pay that director a prorated retainer based on the number of days remaining in the calendar year. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Equity Compensation &#150; Annual Equity Grant </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Annual equity grants are made
following the annual meeting of shareholders. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">If the Board appoints a non-employee director during the year (i.e., other than at the annual meeting of
shareholders), the director receives a prorated equity grant upon appointment. We calculate the value of the prorated grant using this ratio: the number of months until the next annual meeting of shareholders over a denominator of twelve months.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Non-employee director annual equity grants are made in the form of vested deferred stock units. Distribution of actual shares occurs six months after the director
ends his or her service as a director. When the Company pays a dividend on the Company&#146;s common shares, we accrue the value of the dividends that the Company would have paid on the deferred stock units. Six months after the director ends his or
her service as a director, we issue shares to the director equal to the accumulated accrued value. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Stock Ownership Guidelines </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To align further our non-employee directors&#146; interests with our shareholders&#146; interests, we expect our non-employee directors to hold shares of our Common
Stock in an amount equal to five times the annual Board retainer (i.e., $550,000) within five years of becoming a director. If a non-employee director does not meet the stock ownership guidelines within that timeframe, the Lead Director will
consider the non-employee director&#146;s particular situation and may take action, as he deems appropriate. As of March&nbsp;9, 2016, each director who has served for at least five years met or exceeded this requirement. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;31 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Company Match for Director Charitable Contributions </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Non-employee directors are eligible to participate in a Mondel&#275;z International Foundation (the &#147;Foundation&#148;) Matching Gift program. Each year, the
Foundation will generally match up to $15,000 in contributions by a non-employee director to a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization(s). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2015 Non-Employee Director

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The amounts shown in this column represent the full grant date fair value of the deferred stock unit grants in 2015 as computed in accordance with Financial Accounting Standards Board (&#147;FASB&#148;) Accounting
Standards Codification (&#147;ASC&#148;) Topic 718. Assumptions used in the calculation of these amounts are included in Note 11 to the consolidated financial statements contained in our 2015 Form 10-K. The deferred shares are immediately vested,
but receipt of the shares is deferred until six months after the director no longer serves on the Board. The 2015 Non-Employee Director Equity Awards Table below provides further detail on the non-employee director grants made in 2015 and the number
of stock awards outstanding as of December&nbsp;31, 2015. </TD></TR></TABLE>

<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Our 2015 Shareholder Say on Pay Vote Showed Strong Support for Our Executive Compensation Program </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">More than 96% of the votes cast in our 2015 shareholder advisory Say on Pay voted for our executive compensation program. As evidenced by this strong support, we believe
our shareholders generally support our overall compensation principles, programs and practices. Therefore, we made no changes to our executive compensation program directly in response to the 2015 shareholder advisory Say on Pay vote. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Our 2015 Executive Compensation Program Changes to Refine the Alignment with Our Strategies and Objectives </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Compensation Committee regularly assesses our executive compensation program in light of our strategy, market practices and shareholder input. In 2015, we made
changes to our executive compensation program to refine the alignment with our strategies and objectives. We summarize the changes below. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>2015 Annual Cash
Incentive Program Changes </I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="18%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="40%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="40%"></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#4c4c4c" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Item</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Change</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Rationale</FONT></B></FONT></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><I>Calculation of Financial and Individual Performance</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">Separated financial and individual performance. Financial performance now represents 60% of the annual incentive award while individual performance represents 40%. Prior to 2015, we multiplied
the financial performance rating by the individual performance rating.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">Rewards executives for the Company&#146;s financial performance and provides a clear line of sight to executing on strategic individual
goals.</TD></TR></TABLE>
